    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Note concerning the solution where we replaceNode the provided container:\n- for some people having already references to the `<input>`: they will be surprised\n- it's not yet possible with react to render a component inside a dom fragment (and we will need one to replace the node)\n\nSo vanilla JS is the only obvious solution\n",
